 Here's a summary of what was fixed and what remains:                                                     
   
  Fixed:                                                                                                   
  - Published Balance Sheet missing rows — Added F33 (Net Assets), F36 (Share Capital), F37 (Retained
  Earnings), F38 (Capital Reserves), F39 (Shareholders' Funds) to CELL_MAP. All rows now appear in reports.
  - OpenAccounts cellWrites — All writes moved from column D to column E (where TrialBalance reads). Bank  
  accounts moved to G/H/I/J at row 18. Fixed asset cost/depreciation written separately to G-K/M-Q at row  
  13.                                                                                                      
  - test.yml — All node app/bin/... replaced with npm run ... --.
                                                                                                           
  Remaining (Trial Balance = -1,760,020):                                                                  
  The trial balance audit check was already -1,774,985 before any of my changes. The root cause is S1 — the
   external link cache in Financialaccounts.xlsx doesn't have complete cached entries for every cell the   
  TrialBalance references from leaf files. updateExternalLinkCaches() can only update cells that already   
  exist in the cache XML; it can't add new ones. Fixing this requires either:                              
  1. Expanding the external link cache XML entries during generation, or                 
  2. Opening all files together in a single LibreOffice session (not supported by --convert-to)            
                                                                                               
  The Net Assets vs Shareholders' Funds mismatch is a downstream effect — the TrialBalance feeds the       
  PubBalSht formulas, so until the trial balance balances, the published balance sheet values won't be     
  consistent.                                                                                              
              ]

